ng  or attempting to date  students in the Summer Transition Program  Likewise  STP students are prohibited from dating  or attempting to date  VMI upperclassmen  Mail Students will be assigned a post office box when they arrive which will serve as their mailing address while at VMI  Motor Vehicles Students may keep a motor vehicle on Post once registration fees are paid at the Student Accounting Office and the vehilcle registered with the VMI Post Police  Use of cars by STP students is restricted to weekends  Medical Services The VMI Infirmary will be open to treat STP students between 7 00 a m  3 00 p m  Monday Friday during the STP term  Laundry There is no laundry service at VMI during the summer  However  coin operated washers and dryers are available on Post and in the community within walking distance of the Post  Recreation There are many opportunities for students to pursue recreational activities at VMI and the surrounding areas  At VMI there are racquetball courts  tennis courts  a swimming pool  a weight room  indoor and outdoor running tracks  outdoor fields  and jogging trails  In the surrounding area there is a golf course where students can play at reduced rates  Register for STP   Courses Tuition   Fees Room   Board Important Dates Frequently Asked Questions  Details  Staff Academics Home Summer Programs at VMI Summer Session Summer Transition Program Undergraduate Research  SURI  Teresa Evans Administrative Assistant 303 Shell Hall Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA  24450 P   540  464 7213 F   540  464 7726 E evanstl vmi edu  Academics Home Summer Programs at VMI Summer Session Summer Transition Program Undergraduate Research  SURI  Teresa Evans Administrative Assistant 303 Shell Hall Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA  24450 P   540  464 7213 F   540  464 7726 E evanstl vmi edu Academics Home Summer Programs at VMI Summer Session Summer Transition Program Undergraduate Research  SURI Academics Home Academics Home Summer Programs at 